[SN]TITLE[SN]
Southport: Richard Brodie, Luke Foster and Scott Kay sign

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Southport have signed striker Richard Brodie, defender Luke Foster and midfielder Scott Kay.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Brodie, 26, spent time on loan with the Sandgrounders from Gateshead last term, scoring once in 17 league outings.
He also had a spell playing under new Southport manager Martin Foyle at York.
Former Stevenage and Preston centre-back Foster, 28, joins from Lincoln, while Kay, 24, played 27 league games in the Conference Premier for Macclesfield Town last season.
